               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18271206-218-person1181">
                  ROBERT 
                  LUSHER
               <interp inst="t18271206-218-person1181" type="surname" value="LUSHER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18271206-218-person1181" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18271206-218-person1181" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am in the employ of Messrs. James Morrison and Co.; the prisoner came to our shop on the 16th of November; he had been served by another person, but I saw him put a piece of ribbon under the cuff of his coat; I spoke to Smith, who came and stood by me, while the prisoner paid for what he had bought; he then requested him to turn his cuff up, which he did, and this ribbon fell on the counter.</p>
               <p>
            
